node.text: The living legend @MikeHornExplorer tells us about the horrible scenes he has witnessed during his adventures and the importance of the young generations in the race to save our planet ! We must all get together now and start moving, it’s time for action ! Our special thanks to @spgrytz for supporting our vision towards a sustainable environment! #DiscoverEarth

node.text:
Postcards from Turkey 🍃 Have you ever been to this beautiful country before?

Turkey has 44 national parks that look after its stunning natural heritage – so if you decide to visit, you’ll have plenty of options to choose from (some of our favourites are the Yedigoller National Park and the Saklikent Milli Park). 🌳🇹🇷

📍Turkey

🇹🇷 #discoverTurkey with @cumacevikphoto

node.text:
Nothing compares to Australia’s beaches via @mitch_tiktokz 🌊😍 Would you spend the day on the beachside? 

Australia has endless beautiful beaches, so it might take a while to find the perfect one. If you’re looking for something calm and slightly more hidden from tourists, head to the Bailey Beach in Perth or the Mungo beach along the Myall Lakes National Park. Meanwhile, if you’re after something more popular and lively, the iconic Surfers Paradise Beach or Bondi Beach will make you fall in love with the country. 🏖️

📍Australia

🇦🇺 #discoverAustralia
Video by @mitch_tiktokz

Autumn walks in Finland 🍁✨ Have you seen Finland in the fall season before?

Nature’s wonders 🤯 Located along the floor of the Atlantic Ocean, the Mid-Atlantic Ridge is the most extensive chain of mountains of earth, but less than 10% of the range is actually visible for us. There are very few places where the range isn’t hidden, and Iceland is one of the only places where you can see and even stand on this breathtaking ridge. Would you visit this area?

📍 Iceland

🇮🇸 #discoverIceland with @zynl_ozturk

Exploring unknown territory 🧊 This beautiful puma was spotted wandering around the icebergs of Patagonia, Argentina (luckily we don't have to worry, the officials of the Los Glaciares National Park confirmed that the puma isn’t in danger 🙏 )

📍Patagonia, Argentina

🇦🇷 #discoverArgentina with @luigi.fotografia.en.patagonia

node.text:
Real life fairytale village 🌿 Would you visit Lauterbrunnen?

This picturesque village is located in the Swiss alps. Fringed by rocky cliffs, vibrant greens and waterfalls, this spot is one of the most impressive valleys of the area. ⛰️

Insider tip: Although it’s mostly known as an expansive skiing spot during winter, Lauterbrunnen is just as pretty during summer (and it’s perfect for hiking!).

📍Lauterbrunnen, Switzerland

🇨🇭 #discoverSwitzerland with @thetravelergene
